{{defdate|circa 1680}} From [[sashes]], from {{etyl|fr|en}} {{term|châssis||frame (of a window or door)|lang=fr}}, taken as a plural and -s trimmed off by 1704. See also [[chassis]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun|es}}

# The opening part of a [[window]] usually containing the [[glass]] [[panes]], hinged to the [[jamb]], or sliding up and down as in a [[sash window]].
# {{context|software|graphical user interface|lang=en}} A draggable [[vertical]] or [[horizontal]] bar used to adjust the relative sizes of two [[adjacent]] [[window]]s.
# In a [[sawmill]], the [[rectangular]] [[frame]] in which the [[saw]] is [[strain]]ed and by which it is carried up and down with a reciprocating motion; the [[gate]].

